<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
Recently described species from Wuyi Mountains of Fujian Province. Head brown, wider than pronotum; ocelli pale brown; antennae and palpi light brown. Pronotum brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F8002500" captionText="Figure 10. Rhopalopsole wuyishanensis Yang &amp; Du, 2021. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view. Modified from Yang et al. (2021)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711854" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">10</figureCitation>
A). Tergum 10 bearing a large central plate covered with broad sensilla basiconica patch in the lower half and somewhat less sclerotized in the upper half. Lateral projections of tergum 10 plate-like, extending backwards with rectangular-shaped process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F8002500" captionText="Figure 10. Rhopalopsole wuyishanensis Yang &amp; Du, 2021. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view. Modified from Yang et al. (2021)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711854" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
